==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[φιλο-]] ''(philo-,'' love of) + [[ἀτέλεια]] ''(atelīa),'', via French:."Stamp-collecting," 1865, coined by Fr. stamp collector Georges Herpin (in "Le Collectionneur de Timbres-poste," Nov. 15, 1864), the closest word he could find in ancient Greek to the concept of "postage stamp" (from a- "without" + telos "tax"). A reminder of the original function of postage stamps, now often forgotten: the cost of letter-carrying formerly was paid by the recipient; stamps indicated it had been pre-paid by the sender, thus the letters were "carriage-free." Note: French is the international language of philately.

===Noun===
'''philately'''

# [[stamp|Stamp]] [[collecting]].
# The [[study]] of [[postage]] [[stamps]], [[postal]] routes, postal history, etc.

